aas:election_record.label: Georgia 1796 Election Returns for Presidential Electors

aas:ballot.aas:note: Brackets indicate a name that is likely but not certain due to obscured handwriting. A question mark indicates the position of a name that was unreadable.

aas:overview.aas:note: James Jackson, Edward Telfair, Charles Abercrombie, and William Barnett were chosen as the electors from Georgia.
The Southern Centinel notes that James Jackson, Edward Telfair, Charles Abercrombie, and William Barnett are "said to have voted for Jefferson and Clinton" as President and Vice-President.
There was no Federalist slate for electors in 1820 as they ran no candidate for President that year.

These vote totals are taken mainly from the Official Handwritten Vote Returns, and the Augusta Chronicle from December 17, 1796. The other sources mainly agree, although there may be a few differences in vote totals.

aas:sub_unit.name: Effingham
aas:sub_unit.aas:note: It isn't completely clear if the votes for Baldwin and Sam Hammond are from this county or from the county of Franklin.
